[1] Colorado (Mesa county)
Date: Wed 31 Oct 2018 04:55 MDT
Source: Western Slope Now [edited]
https://www.westernslopenow.com/news/local-news/mcph-warns-about-whooping-cough/1565265741


Katie Nelson from Mesa County Public Health stopped by the KREX 5 News Studios to tell us about the vaccinations that can prevent pertussis, also known as whooping cough. Last year [2017], there were 46 cases of whooping cough, and this year there have already been 13.

Mesa County Public Health offers DTaP [diphtheria, tetanus, pertussis] and Tdap [booster] immunizations and accepts all major health insurance plans. They do have programs for those without insurance, and they said cost should not be a barrier to protecting your family. To learn more, visit Mesa County Public Health's immunization section of their website (https://health.mesacounty.us/services/family/immunizations/#1485903122632-690d846f-da4d).

[Byline: Colette Bordelon]

