[6] Saskatchewan
Date: Fri 9 Nov 2018
Source: paNOW [edited]
https://www.panow.com/article/802344/whooping-cough-cluster-south-pa


An outbreak of whooping cough in the Rosthern, Wakaw, Hague, Hepburn, and Waldheim areas in recent weeks prompted the Health Authority to run special drop-in immunization clinics in Rosthern the last 2 days.

The Saskatchewan Health Authority said in an email to paNOW, the majority of children are not up to date or only partially immunized against pertussis.

The cluster of cases since [1 Oct 2018] had seen a total of 22 people with the disease, and one infant had been hospitalized. Over half of the cases were among children under the age of 5. 36 per cent of the cases involved children between 5 and 14 years, with the remainder between 15 and 19 years.

There was no specific number on the amount of people who attended the special drop-in clinic in Rosthern Thursday and Friday [8, 9 Nov 2018] although Dr Chokani said things had been "steady."

[Byline: Glenn Hicks]

